{
  "type": "USJ",
  "version": "3.1",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "book",
      "marker": "id",
      "code": "TIT",
      "content": [
        "EN_ULT"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "h",
      "content": [
        "Titus"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "mt1",
      "content": [
        "The Letter of Paul to"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "mt2",
      "content": [
        "Titus"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "is",
      "content": [
        "Introduction"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "ip",
      "content": [
        "This is a letter from Paul to Titus."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "chapter",
      "marker": "c",
      "number": "1"
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "p",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "1"
        },
        "Paul, a ",
        {
          "type": "char",
          "marker": "bd",
          "content": [
            "servant"
          ]
        },
        " of God and an ",
        {
          "type": "char",
          "marker": "bd",
          "content": [
            "apostle"
          ]
        },
        " of Jesus Christ, for the faith of God's chosen people and the knowledge of the truth.\n",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "2"
        },
        "These are in hope of eternal life that God, who does not lie, ",
        {
          "type": "char",
          "marker": "add",
          "content": [
            "promised"
          ]
        },
        " before all the ages of time.\n",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "3"
        },
        "At the right time, he revealed his word by the message that he trusted me to deliver by the command of God our Savior."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "p",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "4"
        },
        "To Titus, a true son in our common faith. ",
        {
          "type": "note",
          "marker": "f",
          "caller": "+",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fr",
              "content": [
                "1:4 "
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fq",
              "content": [
                "true son "
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "ft",
              "content": [
                "This is a metaphor that means Titus became a Christian through Paul's ministry."
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        "\nGrace and peace from God ",
        {
          "type": "note",
          "marker": "f",
          "caller": "+",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fr",
              "content": [
                "1:4 "
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fq",
              "content": [
                "God "
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "ft",
              "content": [
                "Some versions add "
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fqa",
              "content": [
                "the Father"
              ]
            },
            " ."
          ]
        },
        " and Christ Jesus our Savior.\n\n",
        {
          "type": "ms",
          "marker": "s5",
          "x-bare": "true"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "p",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "5"
        },
        "For this purpose I left you in Crete, that you might set in order things not yet complete and ordain elders in every city as I directed you.\n",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "6"
        },
        "An elder must be without blame, the husband of one wife, with faithful children not accused of reckless behavior or rebellion."
      ]
    }
  ]
}
